---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import YouTubeEmbed from '../components/YouTubeEmbed.astro';
import BuyButton from '../components/BuyButton.astro';
import RegionModal from '../components/RegionModal.astro';
import { qTuneProduct } from '../data/products';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Gift a Q-Tune"
  description="Looking for a meaningful gift for a guitarist? Q-Tune is a DIY tuner pedal kit they build themselves in 15–30 minutes, with no soldering or experience, then use on every gig."
>
  <p class="lead">
    For the guitarist who already owns every pedal but has never built one. Q-Tune is a tuner they
    assemble themselves, with no soldering and no electronics experience, then reach for at every
    practice and every gig.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Why it makes a good gift</h2>

  <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-cream-surface border border-cream-border rounded-xl p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-bold text-text-heading mb-2">They build it themselves</h3>
      <p class="text-text-body leading-relaxed">
        That's the good part. Fifteen to thirty minutes of hands-on assembly, and they get the
        lasting satisfaction of using gear they put together with their own hands.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-cream-surface border border-cream-border rounded-xl p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-bold text-text-heading mb-2">It actually gets used</h3>
      <p class="text-text-body leading-relaxed">
        Every guitarist needs a tuner. This isn't a novelty that ends up in a drawer. It earns a
        permanent spot on their pedalboard.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-cream-surface border border-cream-border rounded-xl p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-bold text-text-heading mb-2">It keeps getting better</h3>
      <p class="text-text-body leading-relaxed">
        Free USB-C firmware updates add new tuning styles and features over time, long after the
        gift is unwrapped.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <h2>Will they be able to build it?</h2>

  <p>
    Yes, that's the whole point of the solderless kit. There's no soldering and no electronics
    experience required. Everything is in the box, down to the hex keys, and most builders finish in
    15–30 minutes. If they ever get stuck, the
    <a href="https://discord.gg/evtjkEj9GX" target="_blank" rel="noopener">builder Discord</a>
    and our support are there to help.
  </p>

  <p>Here's the entire build, start to finish:</p>

  <YouTubeEmbed videoId="cpOn1DBdCLg" title="Q-Tune Assembly Walkthrough" />

  <hr />

  <h2>What's in the box</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Pre-assembled, pre-flashed Q-Tune board</li>
    <li>2.8" touchscreen LCD</li>
    <li>Connectorized footswitch &amp; cables (no soldering)</li>
    <li>All mounting hardware and hex keys</li>
    <li>Painted aluminum enclosure</li>
    <li>Step-by-step assembly guide</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Give one</h2>

  <p>
    Q-Tune is in stock and ships free within the US. If you need it by a particular date,
    <a href="/contact/">reach out</a> and we'll let you know what's possible.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose max-w-xs my-8">
    <BuyButton {...qTuneProduct} />
  </div>

  <RegionModal />
</PageLayout>
